results.name: The next new gap between successive odd primes (divided by 2).
comment: If Polignac's conjecture holds (which is highly likely), then this sequence is a permutation of the positive integers. Even a weaker form of the conjecture would be enough: "Every even number occurs at least once as difference of subsequent primes". - Ferenc Adorjan (ferencadorjan(AT)gmail.com) May 17 2007
